Updating the cluster with the same &lt;major.minor&gt; once it has been created (e.g. 1.14.x -&gt; 1.14) will not trigger an upgrade, even if a newer patch version is available. Updating the cluster with the same &lt;major.minor&gt; once it has been created (e.g. 1.14.x -&gt; 1.14) will not trigger an upgrade, even if a newer patch version is available. Updating the cluster with the same &lt;major.minor&gt; once it has been created (e.g. 1.14.x -&gt; 1.14) will not trigger an upgrade, even if a newer patch version is available. As a best practice, you should upgrade all node pools in an AKS cluster to the same Kubernetes version. The node pool version must have the same major version as the control plane. Updating the cluster with the same &lt;major.minor&gt; once it has been created (e.g. 1.14.x -&gt; 1.14) will not trigger an upgrade, even if a newer patch version is available. Updating the cluster with the same &lt;major.minor&gt; once it has been created (e.g. 1.14.x -&gt; 1.14) will not trigger an upgrade, even if a newer patch version is available. <h4 id="agentpoolupgradesettingsresponse">Agent<wbr>Pool<wbr>Upgrade<wbr>Settings<wbr>Response</h4>



<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="draintimeoutinminutes_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#draintimeoutinminutes_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Drain<wbr>Timeout<wbr>In<wbr>Minutes</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The amount of time (in minutes) to wait on eviction of pods and graceful termination per node. This eviction wait time honors waiting on pod disruption budgets. If this time is exceeded, the upgrade fails. If not specified, the default is 30 minutes.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="maxsurge_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#maxsurge_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Max<wbr>Surge</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>This can either be set to an integer (e.g. '5') or a percentage (e.g. '50%'). If a percentage is specified, it is the percentage of the total agent pool size at the time of the upgrade. For percentages, fractional nodes are rounded up. If not specified, the default is 10%. For more information, including best practices, see: https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/upgrade-cluster#customize-node-surge-upgrade</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="nodesoakdurationinminutes_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#nodesoakdurationinminutes_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Node<wbr>Soak<wbr>Duration<wbr>In<wbr>Minutes</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The amount of time (in minutes) to wait after draining a node and before reimaging it and moving on to next node. If not specified, the default is 0 minutes.</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>
